{"article_id":"EW06lW36nmN24oxU","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"News organizations are convinced","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that the Obama administration trampled on freedom of the press","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"when the Justice Department seized Associated Press phone records in pursuit of a government source","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"who leaked details of a thwarted terrorist plot last year .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"But some congressional analysts also are raising concerns","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"that Justice violated the Constitution ' s separation-of-powers provisions","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"when it targeted the records of reporters","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"working out of a press gallery on Capitol Hill .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"The AP disclosed last week","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"that Justice seized 2012 records of outgoing calls for the work and personal numbers of 20 phone lines","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"assigned to the news service","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"in an attempt","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"to find out","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"who leaked news of the U.S. government ' s intervention of a terrorist plot in Yemen .","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"The phone records were from April and May 2012","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"and included calls","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"made from a main AP number in the House of Representatives press gallery .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"A congressional source said","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"that is particularly unnerving to congressional leadership .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Congress is sensitive about intrusions by the Justice Department ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"which is part of the executive branch ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"into its territory in the legislative branch -","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"and legal analysts familiar with separation-of-powers protections in the Constitution say","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"seizing phone records of journalists","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"working out of a House press gallery","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"raises red flags .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"\" Special concerns are raised","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"if a secretive grab for records extended to those of AP reporters under the auspices of the House gallery , \"","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"said Charles Tiefer , a former House general counsel","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"who is now a professor at the University of Baltimore School of Law .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"\" The House might take strong measures","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"to protect the House press gallery","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"as it has done before","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"- for example , when the FBI raided a congressman ' s office","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"and seized his hard drive and records of his emails . \"","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":3},{"id":36,"text":"Sen. John Cornyn :","depth":4},{"id":37,"text":"' Past time ' for Eric Holder to go","depth":4},{"id":38,"text":"Seven years ago , House Republican and Democratic leaders joined forces","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"to fight another type of Justice Department intrusion","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"- an FBI raid of a sitting congressman ' s Capitol Hill office .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Rep. William J. Jefferson , Louisiana Democrat , was under investigation on charges","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"that he accepted $ 100,000 in bribes","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"for promoting a telecommunication business in Africa .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"He eventually was convicted","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"and went to prison ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"but not before the FBI made a surprise raid on his Capitol Hill office .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"The Justice Department had never raided a congressional office before ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"and the move rattled lawmakers","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"concerned about executive branch overreach .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"House Speaker J. Dennis Hastert , Illinois Republican , and Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi , California Democrat , fought the move in courts in a rare moment of bipartisanship in an otherwise bitterly divided chamber .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"The speech and debate clause of the Constitution forbids any part of the executive branch ,","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"including the Justice Department ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"to impinge on the ability of Congress","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"to legislate in any way .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Even though Jefferson ultimately was found guilty on 11 of 16 corruption charges ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"a federal appeals court ruled","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"that the FBI raid on his office violated the Constitution .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"The ruling was a victory for lawmakers on Capitol Hill","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"because it prevented prosecutors from using some emails and material","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"seized from Jefferson ' s office computers","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"- and the FBI hasn ' t raided a congressional office since .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Former Rep. Dennis J. Kucinich , an Ohio Democrat","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"who lost his seat in the November elections ,","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"raised the separation-of-powers issue in a tweet","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"the day","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"news broke about the Justice Department ' s seizure of AP phone records last week .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"\" Justice Dept probes AP in Congress press gallery attack on 1st Amendment & violation of separation of powers , \"","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"\" This is a question of separation of powers","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"- the same kind of question","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"that was raised","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"when the FBI went in","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"and raided William Jefferson ' s office , \"","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"he said last week .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"\" They did this","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"without notifying congressional leaders .","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"There was no attempt","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"to use the courts ?","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"They have the power","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"to reach in","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"and","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"without any notice ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"reach into an office","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"operated by the House","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"[ of Representatives ] ? \"","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"Rep. Walter B. Jones , North Carolina Republican , differs with Mr. Kucinich on most political matters","depth":4},{"id":87,"text":"but shares his passion","depth":5},{"id":88,"text":"for protecting civil liberties .","depth":5},{"id":89,"text":"He , too , said","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"the revelation","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"that the Justice Department was seizing phone records of AP reporters","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"working out of a House gallery on congressional property","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"smacks of a separation-of-powers violation .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"\" I find this very troubling , \"","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"\" There are conversations","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"that happen between reporters and members of Congress","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"and there are constitutional protections for the press , as well as Congress ,","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"not to have the Justice Department reaching into our branch","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"when it feels like it will help something","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"they are pursuing . \"","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"The House general counsel is looking into the matter","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"but said","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"no separation-of-powers violations exist","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"because the phones in question are not considered House lines ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"according to a congressional source familiar with his thinking .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"The AP pays for all of its phones and lines at its workspace in the Capitol ,","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"and the billing is solely between the carriers and the news agency .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Jan Baran , a partner at the law firm Wiley Rein","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"who specializes in representing members of Congress in ethics matters ,","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"he doesn ' t see direct separation-of-powers issues in this case .","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"\" The AP and its employees are not government officials , let alone congressional officials , \"","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"\" The fact","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"that they work in the House press gallery","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"does not change their status .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"I also am not aware","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"that any congressional documents","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"( including emails on House servers )","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"were subpoenaed or obtained .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"If they were ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"that might raise the separation issue","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"since DOJ would have to refrain from seeing or obtaining legislative data . \"","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"Mr. Kucinich rejects those arguments .","depth":5},{"id":126,"text":"The House of Representatives provides accreditation for journalists","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"working out of the press galleries","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"and even pays for staff","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"to oversee the galleries and assist journalists in procedural matters on Capitol Hill ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"\" To me , the Justice Department","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"[ seizing records of a reporter","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"working out of the House gallery ]","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"is more troubling than anything else [ in the case ] , \"","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"\" I don ' t think","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"there ' s a lot more","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"that has to come out there .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"There are broad protocols about this ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"and they have been violated . \"","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"The AP itself has argued","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"that the seizure of the phone records was unconstitutional on different grounds :","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"as a violation of the First Amendment ' s free press protections .","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"\" We don ' t question their right","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"to conduct these sort of investigations .","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"We just think","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"they went about it the wrong way .","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"So sweeping , so secretively , so abusively , and harassingly and overbroad","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"that it constitutes that it -","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"that it is an unconstitutional act , \"","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"Gary Pruitt , AP president and CEO , said on Sunday ' s \" Face the Nation . \"","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":303,"left":189,"right":302,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":186,"right":188,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":155,"right":185,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":153,"right":154,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":154,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":158,"right":184,"relation":"elaboration","nucle